AGI - &nbsp; At least twenty people fell in water, in Baltimore, overwhelmed by the collapse of a bridge in the American city, collapsed following the impact of a ship. On the bridge, the Francis Scott Key, at the time of the crossing, was also a great auto-articolate and, according to the firefighters, it also poured oil in the river. On the spot came "a team of divers to locate who ended up in water, at least twenty workers".
&nbsp;
< blockquote
BREAKING: Ship collides with Francis Scott Key Bridge in Baltimore, resulting it to collapse <a href="https://t.co/OcOrSjOCRn">pic.twitter.com/OcOrSjOCRn</a> — BNO News (@BNONews)
<a href="https://twitter.com/BNONews/status/1772515766929097088?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw"»March 26, 2024</a>
