According to Baltimore Sun, who mentions a spokesman of the Fire Department, an important rescue operation is underway with the closure of all lanes and the hijacking of traffic from the 1.6-mile steel bridge that is part of Interstate 695.
&nbsp;
"The entire bridge collapsed in the Patapsco River," said Kevin Cartwright, director of communications from the Baltimore Fire Brigade. "We have reason to believe that there have been vehicles and perhaps an auto-articolate" which ended in water, said Cartwright.
&nbsp;
<h2> The jewel of Baltimore
&nbsp;
The Francis Scott Key Bridge was opened in 1977. The intuition is at the American Mameli, the author of the poem of 1814 from which the words of the hymn of the United States, "Star Spangled Banner".
&nbsp;
The steel arched bridge is 2,632 metres long and allows the Interstate 695 road, the 'Baltimore Beltway', to pass the Patapsco River near the port of Maryland. It was crossed on average by 11 million and a half vehicles a year. In the area of the port the river is also crossed by another bridge and a tunnel and are all toll.
&nbsp;
The longest arch of the 'Key Bridge', as it is called by the premises, measures 366 meters and at the time of construction was the third longest in the world for a work of this genre.&nbsp;
