To contest his participation, Le Pen criticized the fact that "not sings in French", his "volgarity" and the "mode of dressing". What an answer, yesterday a group of militants staged a dance to the sound of the music of Nakamura and Piaf. "We are preparing to welcome the whole world for the Olympics, and there is a controversy because some want to symbolically postpone - and not only symbolically - our greatest French artist in Bamako," said Dominique Sopo, president of 'SOS Racisme'.
